# .goosehints — Generic-Improver Integration
# Loaded by dev_rule_refresh_generic.sh
#
# ⛔⛔⛔⛔⛔ RULE SYSTEM ACTIVE
#
# 3 files control your behavior:
#   1. .state/rules/rules.yaml = Your rules + hardness levels
#   2. tools/dev_rule_checker_generic.py = Check rules before actions
#   3. tools/dev_rule_refresh_generic.sh = Reloads rules every 5 steps
#
# HARDNESS LEVELS:
#   ⛔⛔⛔⛔⛔ Hardness 5 = BLOCKED (confirmation required)
#   ⛔⛔⛔      Hardness 4 = Warning (no block)
#   ⛔         Hardness 2 = Notice
#   ⚠️         Hardness 1 = Optional
#
# USAGE:
#   Before each write/edit/shell action:
#     1. bash tools/dev_rule_refresh_generic.sh
#     2. python3 tools/dev_rule_checker_generic.py --all --action "{description}"
#        → Exit code 0 = OK → execute action
#        → Exit code 1 = BLOCKED → ABORT action + inform user
#     3. On BLOCKED: ask user "Execute anyway? (y/N)"
#        → On "y": python3 tools/dev_rule_checker_generic.py --confirm
#        → On "N": DISCARD action
#
# EVERY 5 steps (increment step counter):
#     bash tools/dev_rule_refresh_generic.sh
